
---- tepmlates -----
saves typing, space, 
c++ you can deifne a function template using a generic type

function definition:
template<typname T>

T maxvalue(const t)

takes T& as the arguments

could call 2 integers: maxValue(1, 2);
or could call 2 char: maxValue('a', 'b');
the two can be compared using the > operator (operator overloading)

can put multiple in the same parameters : <typname t1, typname t2, typname t3>

limitations: they must be the same type!!
